<paragraph id="537D36A6FFFDFFE3E1FD07C9FDF7F86E" blockId="5.[151,1437,1938,2038]" box="[199,596,1938,1965]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFDFFE3E1FD07C9FDF7F86E" authority="Seitz, 1909" authorityName="Seitz" authorityYear="1909" box="[199,596,1938,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="mandarina">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFDFFE3E1FD07C9FE68F86E" bold="true" box="[199,459,1938,1965]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">M. phoebe mandarina</emphasis>
Seitz, 1909
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1BD8652DFFFDFFE0E36707C9FBB8FE82" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="537D36A6FFFDFFE0E36707C9FBB8FE82" blockId="5.[151,1437,1938,2038]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,573]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">
[TL Mongolia] a specimen of unspecified sex figured by Seitz (plate 65, fig. h, 1) is large and heavily marked, particularly the forewing post-discal black square spots. 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFDFFE3E58307EDFA3FF812" author="Higgins, L. G." box="[1209,1436,1975,2001]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" pagination="175 - 365" refId="ref9372" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1941) An illustrated catalogue of the Palearctic Melitaea (Lep. Rhopalocera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 91, 175 - 365. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1941. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1941">Higgins (1941: 340)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that it was a form very similar to the taxon 
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFDFFE3E2390781FCDBF836" box="[771,888,2011,2037]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="30">changaica</emphasis>
(see above) and his illustrations (
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFDFFE3E5C30781FA3BF836" author="Higgins, L. G." box="[1273,1432,2011,2037]" pageId="5" pageNumber="30" pagination="175 - 365" refId="ref9372" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1941) An illustrated catalogue of the Palearctic Melitaea (Lep. Rhopalocera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 91, 175 - 365. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1941. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1941">Higgins 1941</bibRefCitation>
: plate 14, figs 7 &amp; 8), show a similarity in spite of the large disparity in size. 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFEFFE0E53D00CDFA3FFF71" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[1031,1436,151,178]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">
<collectingRegion id="9106F844FFFEFFE0E53D00CDFB90FF72" box="[1031,1075,151,177]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">Van</collectingRegion>
Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 60)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that there were 
<specimenCount id="45C4FD2FFFFEFFE0E08C00E1FD97FF16" box="[438,564,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
specimens in the Zoologisches Museum in 
<collectingRegion id="9106F844FFFEFFE0E51C00E1FBCFFF16" box="[1062,1132,187,213]" country="Germany" name="Berlin" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">Berlin</collectingRegion>
(D), they did not illustrate either but placed this form under 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFEFFE0E3300085FD23FF3A" box="[522,640,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFEFFE0E3300085FD23FF3A" box="[522,640,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The underside submarginal markings of specimens illustrated by Seitz and Higgins are curved and touch the intervening veins clearly indicating an association with 
<taxonomicName id="94C24D25FFFEFFE0E58D0159FA8DFEDE" box="[1207,1326,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis id="61B6EAB4FFFEFFE0E58D0159FA8DFEDE" box="[1207,1326,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, agreeing with 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFEFFE0E1EA017DFDF9FE81" author="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G." box="[208,602,295,322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" refId="ref11693" refString="Van Oorschot, H. &amp; Coutsis, J. G. (2014) The genus Melitaea Fabricius, 1807 (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae, Nymphalinae) Taxonomy and systematics with special reference to the male genitalia. Tshikolovets publications, Pardubice, Czech Republic, 360 pp." type="book" year="2014">van Oorschot &amp; Coutsis (2014: 60)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="37534B57FFFEFFE0E3AB017DFC0FFE82" author="Russell, PJ &amp; Tennent, W. J." box="[657,940,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" pagination="27 - 56" refId="ref10922" refString="Russell, PJ. C. &amp; Tennent, W. J. (2016) A synonymic list of names associated with western Palaearctic Melitaea phoebe (Denis &amp; Schiffermuller, 1775) species group taxa M. phoebe; M. punica Oberthur, 1876; M. ornata Christoph, 1893) (Lepidoptera, Nymphalidae). Nota Lepidopterologica, 39 (1), 27 - 56. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / nl. 39.5929" type="journal article" year="2016">Russell &amp; Tennent (2016</bibRefCitation>
: note 49).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
